OL,3,CDad found guilty of 'horrifically'
OL,4,Cmurdering two-year-old son
OL,6,FIn an interview with Lancashire
OL,7,FPolice, Hardcastle gave a prepared
OL,8,Fstatement repeating that Damion had
OL,9,Finjured himself when he ran into the
OL,10,Fcoffee table and had then began
OL,11,Ffitting.
OL,13,FBut Hardcastle's mobile phone revealed
OL,14,Fthat he had made several searches on
OL,15,Fthe internet on how long it takes
OL,16,Fbruises heal, with one search just
OL,17,Ffour minutes before his 999 call.
OL,19,FThe 31-year-old father made no comment
OL,20,Fin a subsequent police interview and
OL,21,Fwent on to plead not guilty.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/7
