OL,3,CDad found guilty of 'horrifically'
OL,4,Cmurdering two-year-old son
OL,6,FDet Supt Al Davies, of the Force Major
OL,7,FInvestigation Team, said: "Like any
OL,8,Fyoung child Damion had the right to be
OL,9,Floved and cherished by the man who
OL,10,Fshould have done everything he could
OL,11,Fto protect him.
OL,13,F"Instead, he found himself subjected
OL,14,Fto a horrifically violent and
OL,15,Fsustained assault which caused the
OL,16,Finjuries which sadly led to his death.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G6/7
