OL,3,CDad found guilty of 'horrifically'
OL,4,Cmurdering two-year-old son
OL,6,F"Only Daniel Hardcastle can say
OL,7,Fexactly what happened on that fateful
OL,8,Fday or why he did what he did, but
OL,9,Fthis was no childhood accident that
OL,10,Fended in tragedy.
OL,12,F"The nature and extent of the fatal
OL,13,Finjuries, deliberately inflicted by
OL,14,FHardcastle were done with intent to
OL,15,Fcause at least really serious harm and
OL,16,Fwere the direct cause of Damion's
OL,17,Ftragic death."
OL,19,FHardcastle, 31, will be sentenced at a
OL,20,Flater date.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G7/7
